merica":"布利提申 可隆尼亞爾 亞美利加南卡罗来纳州","lifeSummary":"Edna Perrin是William Perrin的女儿，于1560年出生在英国英格兰諾福爾可。她于大约1577年与George Heard结婚。他们至少是2个儿子的父母。她去世于1608年在布利提申 可隆尼亞爾 亞美利加南卡罗来纳州享年48岁。"},"hr":{"1560–1608":"1560.–1608.","1560–1628":"1560.–1628","1578–1626":"1578.–1626","1580–1626":"1580.–1626","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1535":"1535","1578":"1578.","1599":"1599","1560":"1560.","about 1577":"oko 1577.","27 Jan 1599":"27. siječnja 1599.","1608":"1608.","1580":"1580.","1628":"1628","1626":"1626","Clinton, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Clinton, Yaxham, Norfolk, England":"Yaxham, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, Engleska, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","South Carolina, British Colonial America":"South Carolina, British Colonial America"},"cs":{"1560–1608":"1560–1608","1560–1628":"1560–1628","1578–1626":"1578–1626","1580–1626":"1580–1626","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1535":"1535","1578":"1578","1599":"1599","1560":"1560","about 1577":"okolo 1577","27 Jan 1599":"27. ledna 1599","1608":"1608","1580":"1580","1628":"1628","1626":"1626","Clinton, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Clinton, Yaxham, Norfolk, England":"Yaxham, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","South Carolina, British Colonial America":"South Carolina, British Colonial America"},"da":{"1560–1608":"1560–1608","1560–1628":"1560–1628","1578–1626":"1578–1626","1580–1626":"1580–1626","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1535":"1535","1578":"1578","1599":"1599","1560":"1560","about 1577":"omkring 1577","27 Jan 1599":"27. januar 1599","1608":"1608","1580":"1580","1628":"1628","1626":"1626","Clinton, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Clinton, Yaxham, Norfolk, England":"Yaxham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","South Carolina, British Colonial America":"South Carolina, British Colonial America"},"nl":{"1560–1608":"1560–1608","1560–1628":"1560–1628","1578–1626":"1578–1626","1580–1626":"1580–1626","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1535":"1535","1578":"1578","1599":"1599","1560":"1560","about 1577":"circa 1577","27 Jan 1599":"27 januari 1599","1608":"1608","1580":"1580","1628":"1628","1626":"1626","Clinton, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Clinton, Yaxham, Norfolk, England":"Yaxham, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","South Carolina, British Colonial America":"South Carolina, British Colonial America"},"en":{"1560–1608":"1560–1608","1560–1628":"1560–1628","1578–1626":"1578–1626","1580–1626":"1580–1626","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1535":"1535","1578":"1578","1599":"1599","1560":"1560","about 1577":"about 1577","27 Jan 1599":"27 January 1599","1608":"1608","1580":"1580","1628":"1628","1626":"1626","Clinton, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Clinton, Yaxham, Norfolk, England":"Yaxham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","South Carolina, British Colonial America":"South Carolina, British Colonial America","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Perrin","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French and English: from the Old French and Middle English personal name <i>Perrin</i>, a pet form of Old French <i>Perre</i>, a variant of   Pierre  , French form of   Peter  . Compare   Perine  ,   Perrine  , and   Prine  .","History: Henri Perrin from Louargat in Côtes-d'Armor, Brittany (France), married Jeanne Merrin in Montreal, QC, in 1661. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (along with its variants or altered forms <i>Perrine</i> and <i>Pareyn</i>) and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America. One of the Huguenot ancestors was Daniel Perrin (1642–1719), nicknamed <i>The Huguenot</i>, who arrived in New York in 1665, aboard the <i>Philip</i>, and settled first in NJ and later on Staten Island. Among his descendants the surname is common in the altered forms <i>Perrine</i>, <i>Perine</i> and <i>Prine</i>. The Staten Island community of Huguenot is named after Daniel Perrin and other Huguenots who settled in the area during the late 17th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Prine","meanings":["Americanized form of French   Perrin  .","In some cases also an Americanized form of Dutch   Pruyn   or perhaps of some other similar (like-sounding) surname.","History: The surname <i>Prine</i> is established among the descendants of the Huguenot immigrant Daniel Perrin (1642–1719); see   Perrin  ."]},{"name":"Pierre","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Jacques, Antoine, Yves, Michel, Jean Claude, Mireille, Jean Robert, Francois, Monique, Raoul, Serge.","French, Walloon, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and Mauritian:","from the personal name <i>Pierre</i>, French form of   Peter   (see also below). This is one of the most frequent surnames in Haiti (along with   Jean   and   Joseph  ) and in Saint Martin. It is also established elsewhere in the West Indies (e.g. in Trinidad and Tobago, Saint Lucia, Grenada, and Bahamas)."]},{"name":"Perren","meanings":["French and English (of French Huguenot origin): variant of   Perrin  ."]},{"name":"Parren","meanings":["English: variant of   Perrin  ."]},{"name":"Perrine","meanings":["French: from the feminine form of   Perrin   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","English: variant of   Perrin  . This surname is now rare in Britain and Ireland.","History: The surname <i>Perrine</i> of French origin (see 1 above) is listed along with its original form   Perrin   in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Parran","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Monique.","Altered form of French   Perrin  . This surname was brought to England by the Huguenots, but has died out there.","In some cases possibly also southern French: topographic name from Occitan <i>parran</i> ‘small garden behind a house’. This surname is very rare in France."]},{"name":"Perrins","meanings":["English (West Midlands): variant of   Perrin  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Edna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["In Ireland this has been used as an Anglicized form of Eithne . The name occurs in the apocryphal Book of Tobit, where it is the name of the mother of Sarah and stepmother of Tobias. This is said to be from Hebrew <i>῾ednah</i> ‘pleasure, delight’, and if so it is connected with the name of the Garden of   Eden .  The earliest known uses of the given name in England are in the 16th century, when it was probably imported from Ireland, although the spelling <i>Ednah</i> supports the idea that it was taken from the Bible."],"variants":[{"name":"Eithne","meanings":["Traditional name, apparently from <i>eithne</i> ‘kernel’, which was used as a term of praise in bardic poetry. St Eithne was a daughter of King Laoghaire and one of St Patrick's first converts."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Edna Perrin was born in 1560, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of William Perrin. She married George Heard about 1577. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1608, in South Carolina, British Colonial America, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1560–1608":"1560–1608","1560–1628":"1560–1628","1578–1626":"1578–1626","1580–162